; Unsatisfiable incoming view propagates into the reading TUPLE.
; Two unsat shapes feed `out`:
;   - `impossible` joins facts with conflicting constants (1 vs 2), which
;     constant propagation marks unsat, and the TUPLE reading it follows;
;   - `also_impossible` constrains one variable to two different constants.
; Only the `possible` arm may ever produce rows.

#message input(i32 X).
#local bar(i32 A).
#local baz(i32 A).
#local impossible(i32 A).
#local also_impossible(i32 X).
#local possible(i32 X).
#query out(free i32 X).

bar(1).
baz(2).
impossible(A) : bar(A), baz(A).
also_impossible(X) : input(X), X = 1, X = 2.
possible(X) : input(X), X = 3.
out(X) : impossible(X).
out(X) : also_impossible(X).
out(X) : possible(X).
